    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-02-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="542"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/740.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On the 6th instant the Mexican Embassy addressed to the Department of State a
                    memorandum stating that persistent rumors have reached Mexico that in some towns
                    of Texas [etc.].</p>
                <p>The Department of State has taken pleasure in sending copies of the memorandum
                    from the Mexican Embassy to the Secretary of War and the Attorney General for
                    their information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
